      <td>Specifically, the L1 norm and the L2 norm differ in how they achieve their objective of small weights, so understanding this can be useful for deciding which to use..  On the one hand, L1 wants errors to be all or nothing, which leads to sparse weights since all the errors are concentrated in one place.  As a simple example, letâ€™s say there are six weights, then L1 =</td>
